  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "`buidler-solhint` fails if `eslint` is also installed, as it assumes that it can just `require` `solhint`'s `eslint` version.\r\n\r\nThe problem comes from [this line](https://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/master/packages/buidler-solhint/src/index.ts#L14), where an internal `eslint` module is required, without having `eslint` declared as a dependency.\r\n\r\nIt should be something like this, to ensure that the `buidler-solhint` and `solhint` are using the same `eslint` version:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst solhintPath = require.resolve(\"solhint\");\r\nconst formatterPath = require.resolve(`eslint/lib/formatters/${formatterName}`, {paths: [solhintPath]});\r\nreturn require(formatterPath);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThank you @paxthemax for reporting and investigating this issue!\r\n\r\n",
